  <title>Oracle JDeveloper Extensions</title>
  <para>
    Oracle JDeveloper is an integrated development environment (IDE) for building applications using the latest standards for Java, XML, Web services, and SQL.
    Most of the basic functionality in JDeveloper is implemented as extensionsâ€”software packages which add features and capabilities to the basic JDeveloper IDE.
    You can add existing extensions into JDeveloper, or you can build on JDeveloper's native functionality by creating extensions to provide new features tailored to your organization's development requirements, for example:
  </para>
  <itemizedlist mark='bullet'>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        To streamline your work flow.
      </para>
      <para/>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        To use a third-party team development tool.
      </para>
      <para/>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        To use software packages unique to your team.
      </para>
      <para/>
      <para/>
    </listitem>
    <listitem>
      <para>
        To help implement development standards and best practices with audit extensions.
      </para>
    </listitem>
  </itemizedlist>
  <para>
    There are a wide variety of extensions readily available for you to download and use.
    Some of these have been developed by Oracle, and some by third parties.
    These provide new features to JDeveloper and integrate it with other applications that are used by customers in their own development environments.
    For example, many of the version control and teamworking systems available in JDeveloper are written and distributed as extensions.
    The open architecture of JDeveloper means that you can download and install them from <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates</emphasis> on the JDeveloper <emphasis role="strong">Help</emphasis> menu.
    Alternatively, you can install them from the Oracle JDeveloper Extensions page on the Oracle Technology Network (OTN) at https://www.oracle.com/webfolder/technetwork/jdeveloper/downloads/1213center.xml
  </para>
  <note>
    The recommended way of installing extensions to JDeveloper is to use <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates</emphasis> on the JDeveloper <emphasis role="strong">Help</emphasis> menu because only extension versions that match the version of JDeveloper you are using will be available.
  </note>
  <para>
    For more information, see "Working with Extensions" in Oracle Fusion Middleware User Guide for Oracle JDeveloper.
    <link xl:show="new"
          xl:href="https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E16162_01/user.1112/e17455/working_jdev.htm#OJDUG4745"
          xl:role="http://docbook.org/xlink/role/olink">
      <citetitle>"Working with Extensions"</citetitle>
    </link>
    in
    <link xl:show="new"
          xl:href="https://docs.oracle.com/cd/E16162_01/user.1112/e17455/toc.htm"
          xl:role="http://docbook.org/xlink/role/olink">
      <citetitle>Oracle Fusion Middleware User Guide for Oracle JDeveloper</citetitle>
    </link>
  </para>
  <section xml:id="about-ide-01">
    <title>Configure Update Center</title>
    <para>
      To avoid the hassle of selecting the right version, let JDeveloper do this work for you.
      We simply add the URL of the Identity and Aceess Management Extension to the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> and JDeveloper will search for extensions compatible to your JDeveloper version.
    </para>
    <para>
      If you ever used the <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates...</emphasis> feature in JDeveloper, we are sure you've seen the list of available <emphasis role="strong">Update Centers</emphasis> from which you can download your JDeveloper extensions.
      In this section we will go through the process of adding a <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> that supply the maintenance for the JDeveloper Extension.
    </para>
    <orderedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          You can access the <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates...</emphasis> feature in JDeveloper via the <emphasis role="strong">Help</emphasis> | <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates...</emphasis> menu.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>menu</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/001.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Once you did so, a list of the available Update Centers is presented as shown in the picture below.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>menu</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/center/002.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <note>
          <para>
            It's wisly to switch of the option <emphasis role="strong">Automatically check for updates at startup</emphasis> at the top of the dialog.
          </para>
        </note>
        <para>
          It is easy to add a new <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> by clicking on the <emphasis role="strong">Add...</emphasis> button.
        </para>
        <para/>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Supplying the necessary information, i.e. the name of the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> and its location.
        </para>
        <table frame="topbot" colsep="0" rowsep="1">
          <tgroup cols="2">
        <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="8em"/>
        <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="*"/>
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry>Option</entry>
                <entry>Value</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry><emphasis role="strong">Name</emphasis></entry>
                <entry><literal>Oracle Consulting Updates</literal></entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry><emphasis role="strong">Location</emphasis></entry>
                <entry><literal>https://cms.cinnamonstar.dev/software/ide/oracle.ocs.workspace.iam-12.2.1.xml</literal></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>menu</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/center/003.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <note>
          <para>
            Location is the http address of the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> descriptor in this example, note the extensions itself.
          </para>
        </note>
        <para>
          Click <emphasis role="strong">Ok</emphasis> to add the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para/>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          After adding the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis>, the <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates...</emphasis> page will reflect the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> added as it is shown below.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>menu</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/center/004.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
        <para/>
      </listitem>
      <listitem>
        <para>
          Selecting the newly added <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> and clicking <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis> will present a list of the extensions that are made available by the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis>.
        </para>
        <para>
          <mediaobject>
            <alt>menu</alt>
            <imageobject>
              <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/center/005.png" format="PNG"/>
            </imageobject>
          </mediaobject>
        </para>
      </listitem>
    </orderedlist>
  </section>
  <section xml:id="about-iam-01">
    <title>Identity and Aceess Management Extension</title>
    <para>
      This section describes the installation, configuration and usage of the Identity and Aceess Management Extension.
    </para>
    <section xml:id="about-iam-01-01">
      <title>Install</title>
      <important>
        <para>
          The JDeveloper plug-in requires JDeveloper 12c (12.2.1.3) or later.
        </para>
      </important>
      <para>
        You can install the extension directly from inside JDeveloper through the <emphasis role="strong">Help</emphasis> | <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates</emphasis> menu option which is the recommended way to install extensions.
      </para>
      <important>
        <para>
          The extension itself is not provided by the official <emphasis role="strong">Oracle JDeveloper Extension Exchange</emphasis> portal.
        </para>
        <para>
          If you would like to manage the extension like the officials you should configure JDeveloper following the instructions <link linkend="about-ide-01">Configure Update Center</link>.
        </para>
      </important>
      <para>
        To make the <emphasis role="strong">Identity and Access Management</emphasis> extension available in Oracle JDeveloper 12c perform following steps:
      </para>
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Open Oracle JDeveloper 12c if it is not already open.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Navigate to the menu <emphasis role="strong">Help</emphasis> | <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates...</emphasis>.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>menu</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/001.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            This opens the Check for Update Wizard of Oracle JDeveloper 12c.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Select only that <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> which you configured by <link linkend="about-ide-01">Configure Update Center</link>.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>install</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/install/002.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <note>
            <para>
              If JDeveloper isn't able to access the internet advice in the <emphasis role="strong">Select update source</emphasis> page to use the local file you have downloaded.
            </para>
          </note>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis>.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            After the <emphasis role="strong">Update Center</emphasis> analyzed the extension descriptor select the correct version.
          </para>
          <important>
            <para>
              You need switch on the checkbox in front of the extension name.
            </para>
          </important>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>license</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/install/003.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis>.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            You need to accept the license aggrement.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>aggrement</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/install/004.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            In the <emphasis role="strong">License Agreements</emphasis> review the license and click <emphasis role="strong">I Agree</emphasis> to indicate that you accept the terms.
            JDeveloper confirms that you agreed to the license.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>accepted</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/install/005.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Next</emphasis>.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            After the Update Wizard analyzed the archive review in the <emphasis role="strong">Summary</emphasis> that you picked up the correct version.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>accepted</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/install/006.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Finish</emphasis> to close the <emphasis role="strong">Check for Updates</emphasis> wizard.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            You will be ask for to restart Oracle JDeveloper 12c.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>summary</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/install/007.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Yes</emphasis> to restart.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </section>
    <section xml:id="about-iam-01-02">
      <title>Configuration</title>
      <para>
        The extension provides the capabilities to switch off or on specific features.
        The features that you can partially switch on or off are:
      </para>
      <table frame="topbot" colsep="0" rowsep="1">
        <tgroup cols="5">
          <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="3*"/>
          <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="2*"/>
          <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="2*"/>
          <thead>
            <row>
              <entry namest="c1" nameend="c2">Category</entry>
              <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Feature</entry>
            </row>
          </thead>
        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry namest="c1" nameend="c1"><emphasis role="strong">Identity and Access Management</emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c2" nameend="c2"><emphasis>Directory Services</emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Integration Platform</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry namest="c1" nameend="c1"><emphasis role="strong"></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c2" nameend="c2"><emphasis></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Internet Directory</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry namest="c1" nameend="c1"><emphasis role="strong"></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c2" nameend="c2"><emphasis></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Unified Directory</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry namest="c1" nameend="c1"><emphasis role="strong"></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c2" nameend="c2"><emphasis></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Virtual Directory</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry namest="c1" nameend="c1"><emphasis role="strong"></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c2" nameend="c2"><emphasis>Identity Management</emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Identity Manager</entry>
          </row>
          <row>
            <entry namest="c1" nameend="c1"><emphasis role="strong"></emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c2" nameend="c2"><emphasis>Access Management</emphasis></entry>
            <entry namest="c3" nameend="c3">Access Manager</entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>
    <important>
      <para>
        The <emphasis role="strong">Extension Foundation</emphasis> feature cannot switched of.
      </para>
    </important>
      <para>
        Complete the following steps to configure Identity and Access Management extension:
      </para>
      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Open Oracle JDeveloper 12c if it is not already open.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Navigate to the menu <emphasis role="strong">Tools</emphasis> | <emphasis role="strong">Features</emphasis>.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>menu</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/002.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            The <emphasis role="strong">Manage Features and Updates</emphasis> dialog of Oracle JDeveloper 12c apears and display the extensions currently intalled.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            In the tree of <emphasis role="strong">Features</emphasis> scroll down until <emphasis role="strong">Identity and Access Management</emphasis> becomes visible.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>menu</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/feature/002.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            Beneath the feature <emphasis role="strong">Identity and Access Management</emphasis> you find all features that are associated with the extension plug-in.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>menu</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/feature/003.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Select the appropriate features for your needs.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>menu</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/feature/004.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Apply Changes</emphasis>.
          </para>
          <para/>
          <para/>
        </listitem>
        <listitem>
          <para>
            You will be ask for to restart Oracle JDeveloper 12c.
          </para>
          <para>
            <mediaobject>
              <alt>menu</alt>
              <imageobject>
                <imagedata scalefit="1" width="100%" contentdepth="100%" fileref="src/site/extension/images/en/ide/extension/feature/005.png" format="PNG"/>
              </imageobject>
            </mediaobject>
          </para>
          <para>
            Click <emphasis role="strong">Yes</emphasis> to confirm.
          </para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </section>
  </section>
